<ul class="project-title-and-text">

    <li class="project-title">
        Unique Industries, Inc.
    </li>

    <li class="project-type">
        Product / Packaging Development Support
    </li>

    <li class="project-tools">
        Illustrator, Large-Format Printer, Heat Sealing Machine, X-Acto Knife
    </li>

    <li class="project-objective-title">
        About
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        Production design work supporting licensed consumer goods across Disney, Marvel, DC, and Sanrio product lines.
        Focused on mock-up construction, asset management, file preparation, and maintaining accuracy across high-volume
        product lines.
    </li>

    <!-- <li class="project-process-title">
        Process
    </li>

    <li class="project-body-text">
        I received the files from the design team and prepared them for print in Illustrator before
        sending them to the large-format color printer. I then applied the appropriate adhesives to
        adhere them to weighted paper. Some of the products required glitter, so I applied PVA glue to
        the necessary parts before adding the glitter, and allowed the glue to cure for 24 hours. I
        later paired said mock-ups with the appropriate mocked-up packages.
    </li> -->
</ul>

